Name: Dr. Aaron Dishno
AboutMe:
Graduating in 2011 from La Sierra University in Riverside California, Aaron Dishno received his Doctorate in Education (Ed.D.) with an emphasis on Administration and Leadership. He also holds a Master of Science Degree in Education with an emphasis in Educational Technology and a Bachelor of Science Degree in Information Services Management from California Baptist University.

Dr. Aaron Dishno has held the position of Webmaster and Programmer Analyst III for nearly 10 years for the County of San Bernardino, which is the largest county in the USA. He has worked as a computer programmer, mentor, teacher, analyst, electronic repair, network consultant / installer, systems / server integrator, enterprise architect, and cloud architect for an accumulative 25 years.

Dr. Aaron Dishno has patents pending in 3D Internet Browsing and 3D Building Website Design, Holds the trademarks for http://3d, https://3d, http3d, and Walk the Web. To read more, go to WalkTheWeb.com.
